quality matters promotes a peer review process and provides a database of qualified qm peer reviewers eligible for assignment to a peer review team. courses that successfully meet the qm rubric standards in an official (subscriber-managed or qm-managed) course review are eligible for qm recognition. san jose state university has subscribed to the services offered by quality matters. if you are interested in having your course certified, please read about preparing for a quality matters course review , which provides course preparation guidelines and the steps in an official qm-managed course review. prior to completing a course review application, please contact sjsu ecampus at ecampus@sjsu.edu for next steps for a sjsu qm course review. an official course review must meet the following criteria: phone: 408-924-2337 email: ecampus@sjsu.edu location: irc, room 206 ecampus, irc206 instructional resource center san jose state university one washington square san jose, ca 95192-0026 